snippet.textDisplay:
I cannot put my finger on it, but there is just so much about Austin Evan's that just frustrates me to the core, and creeps me out. Could have been good content in this video but idk I couldnt watch this to the end.. Austin you come across so abrasively and so irritating with your dry and humourless, even soul draining approach to 'decent tech tubing' - WHICH ALL SUCKS and all your videos are clickbaity and aimed at millennials -> the ultimate switch lite video I watched yesterday was EMBARRASING YO, I hate to be the negative Nancy here, but you kinda suck bro and you have about as much character integrity as a cardboard cut out of Carole baskin in the act of definitely not killing her husband - Compared to you shilling out hard every video, linus takes some stick but he's atleast not morally bankrupt, p.s. the other staff off camera seem like they do a fuck load of work and production behind the scenes, which definitely shows. The content behind the format here is definitely researched well, it's just austin takes up the limelight with his greasy scalp and lack of personality, I just feel this channel is just for fuelling an ego at this point!

P.s. i wouldnt have posted if i hadn't had watched 1 video and now get CONSTANTLY recommended austin fucking Evan's and it is grossing me out how this guy has any viewers at all! (All about the benjamins)

snippet.textDisplay:
More specifically: Who loses their joycon, while they're powered on?


Edit: In addition to that, if your right joycon and all other controllers with home buttons are missing the only way to get to the home menu is to put the switch into sleep, wake it again, and tap the go home option instead of the game icon when unlocking. Putting the console into sleep automatically also puts all the controllers to sleep. Now your missing joycon is powered off for sure and so you can't track it down with the vibration anyway.
